---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"repo\", \"create\", \"--help\"])"
---
Create a GitHub repo for the current project (lab-manual gh flow)

Creates the repository under the lab org (private by default) via `gh` and wires it up as the origin remote, following the lab-manual flow. `gh` must be authenticated. Pass --yes to accept the defaults without prompting.

Usage: hpds repo create [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --name <NAME>
          Repository name [default: the current directory's name]

  -v, --verbose
          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)

      --org <ORG>
          GitHub organization (or user) to create the repo under [default: StanfordHPDS]

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output except errors

      --no-color
          Disable colored output

      --visibility <VISIBILITY>
          Repository visibility [default: private]
          
          [possible values: private, public]

      --config <PATH>
          Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml

  -y, --yes
          Accept the default for every unanswered question; never prompt

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
